               <head>Sermons, mostly for Lent, with texts on confession; Germany, 1392</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <note>15th-century table of contents pasted on to the upper pastedown.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_Lat_th_e_22-item1">
                     <locus>(fols. 1r–122v)</locus>
                     <title key="work_14583" type="desc">Sermon collection</title>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 1r-115r)</locus>
                        <title type="desc">Sermons for Lent</title>
                        <note>'Quadragesimale bonum' (table of contents)</note>
                        <msItem>
                           <incipit>
                              <cit>
                                 <quote>Tu autem cum ieiunas unge capud tuum</quote>
                                 <bibl>Mt vi.</bibl>
                              </cit> In hoc ieiunii capite necessarium nobis est ut taliter ieiunemus <note>[first sermon]</note>
                           </incipit>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem>
                           <incipit>
                              <cit>
                                 <quote>Homo quidam fecit cenam magnam <gap reason="editorial"/>
                                 </quote>
                                 <bibl>Luc. 14</bibl>
                              </cit> Homo iste est Iesus Christus vt dicit Glossa, qui vt famelicas animas saturaret factus est cibus hominum <note>[last sermon]</note>
                           </incipit>
                        </msItem>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 115r-117r)</locus>
                        <rubric>Sermo communis</rubric>
                        <incipit>
                           <quote>Ecce nunc tempus acceptabile <gap reason="editorial"/>
                           </quote> Notandum est quod triplex est dies. Prima est temporalis vite</incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 117r-118r)</locus>
                        <!-- 237 -->
                        <rubric>De confessione</rubric>
                        <incipit>
                           <quote>Confitemini alter utrum peccata <gap reason="editorial"/>
                           </quote> Circa confessionem salutiferam quinque per ordinem sunt notanda. Primum est quod confessio debet esse festina</incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 118r-119r)</locus>
                        <rubric>Sermo communis</rubric>
                        <incipit>
                           <quote>Confitemini alter utrum etc.</quote> Notandum quod homines tripliciter peccant, ut dicit Ysidorus, primo in patrem per infirmitatem ut gulosi et luxuriosi, et taliter peccauit Dauid</incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 119r-121r)</locus>
                        <rubric>X aliena peccata</rubric>
                        <incipit>
                           <quote>Ab occultis meis munda me domine et ab alienis parce seruo tuo.</quote> Sic orauit sanctus Dauid </incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 121r-122v)</locus>
                        <rubric>Questiones de vij mortalibus peccatis</rubric>
                        <incipit>Queritur de septem viciis capitalium quando quodlibet eorum possit dici mortale et quando veniale, ad quod respondeo secundum Augustinum</incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <!-- <explicit>resurrectionem de lecto et tamen pigrescit hoc facere.</explicit>-->
                     <colophon>Finito libro sit laus et gloria cristo. Expliciunt sermones ewangeliorum completi post <gap quantity="50" reason="cancelled" unit="char"/> anno domini Mº.CCCº.xciiº in die Inuencionis sancte Crucis.</colophon>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_th_e_22-item1-item1">
                        <locus>(fols. 123r–124v)</locus>
                        <title key="work_14583" type="desc">Sermon</title>
                        <rubric>
                           <locus>(fol. 122v)</locus> Sequitur sermo in die parascheue et de sancta cruce</rubric>
                        <incipit>
                           <cit>
                              <quote>Baiolans sibi crucem exiuit in eum qui dicitur calvarie locus</quote>
                              <bibl>Io. 20.</bibl>
                           </cit> Hodie mater ecclesia uniuersis filiis suis</incipit>
                        <explicit>Crux cristi clauis est paradysi.</explicit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_th_e_22-item1-item2">
                        <locus>(fols. 124v–125v)</locus>
                        <title key="work_14583" type="desc">Sermon</title>
                        <rubric>Sermo de eodem</rubric>
                        <incipit>Item preter illa que dicta sunt notanda alia quatuor bona</incipit>
                        <explicit>Vulnerata crura pendant. Cui est honor et gloria in secula seculorum. Amen.</explicit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fol. 125v)</locus>
                        <incipit>Wo man den saltir sal laze lousin. Man sal eyne salm</incipit>
                        <explicit>und sprich disse besc<supplied>h</supplied>werunge.</explicit>
                        <textLang mainLang="de">German </textLang>
                        <note>(Crossed through and effaced.)</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_th_e_22-item2">
                        <locus>(fols. 126r–127v)</locus>
                        <note>Alphabetical subject index to the sermon collection, using both the arabic and roman foliations.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <bibl>Schneyer, <title>Beobachtungen zu lateinischen Sermoneshandschriften der Staatsbibliothek München</title> (1958), no. 5197 (p. 45) lists other copies of a Quadragesimale beginning with the sermon here beginning fol. 1r and ending with the sermon here beginning fol. 123r.</bibl>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_th_e_22-item3">
                     <locus>(fols. 127v–128v)</locus>
                     <title key="work_14583" type="desc">Sermon</title>
                     <rubric>De extremo iudicio</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <quote>Arguet mundum de iudicio quia non timent. quo nichil est terribilius.</quote>
                        <hi rend="underline">Heb. x.</hi> Terribilis quidem est expectacio iudicii</incipit>
                     <explicit>non potest sic et illa summa dampnatorum.</explicit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_th_e_22-item4">
                     <locus>(fols. 128v–130r)</locus>
                     <title key="work_14583" type="desc">Sermon</title>
                     <incipit>
                        <quote>Humiliamini sub potenti manu dei.</quote> iª. pet. ult. Homini remanentem quatuor habere oportet</incipit>
                     <explicit>unam des heiligen geistis.</explicit>
                     <note>'De humilitate sermo' (table of contents)</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="la" otherLangs="de">Latin, with the closing formula in German</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_th_e_22-item5">
                     <locus>(fols. 130v-132v)</locus>
                     <title key="work_15047">Declaraciones breves de concordancia epistolarum et ewangeliorum dominicalium</title>
                     <note>(Title from list of contents on pastedown.)</note>
                     <incipit>Introitus collecta leccio et ewangelium concordant quia peccator</incipit>
                     <explicit>ita monet apostolus ut cum ipso resurgamus.</explicit>
                  </msItem>
