                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notAfter="1500" notBefore="1392">
                        <p>Medieval binding. Sewn on four double bands laced into horizontal channels and pegged into wood (beech?) boards, covered with leather dyed red; the single (intact) strap fastening from the back to the front board with shield-shaped clasp and catch-plates. Fore-edge tabs. The front board with a title ‘Sermones quadragesimales’ writing in a large formal gothic script on a parchment slip, too long to be attached horizontally and therefore placed vertically.</p>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
